						<summary>

						<p>Slab (No. 1) built into the wall of the well called Jēḍara-bāvi.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">17th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that <hi rend="italic">gavuḍa</hi> Dupada Tiṁmaya of Sarajāpura built this well.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Krōdhi, Bhādrapada ba. 3. The details are insufficient for verification. The record is in characters of the 17th century. The cyclic year Krōdhi occurred twice during the 17th century <hi rend="italic">viz.,</hi> (1) Śaka 1526 (1604 A.D.) and (2) Śaka 1586 (1664 A.D.) [Refer No. 315 above]. The probable date of the record may be 1604 A.D., September 1, (Sunday).</p>						

						</summary>
